# Chart Stream Observation: External Sources into Memory

## Destination

External streams — Front, Slack (webhooks already flowing realtime), GitHub,
Twitter, ClickHouse telemetry — flow through the observer's distillation
discipline into the same observation memory: webhook/ping → accumulated raw
events → source epochs → validated, provenance-carrying observation pages
that are ACTIONABLE and worth recalling ("not total dogshit" — Joel's
charter, 2026-07-13). Reached when a Slack decision, a Front escalation, or
a GitHub release lands in memory the same afternoon with the same schema
discipline as session epochs, and the Bugle mines those pages instead of
cold-reading raw sources at 6am.

**This map deliberately redraws a boundary**: the observational-memory map
ruled external streams out of scope ("the Bugle owns it") and VISION.md
echoes it. Per wayfinder doctrine that returns as a fresh effort — this is
it. The redraw itself is a grilling ticket; VISION.md and the old map get
updated only when it resolves.

## Notes

- **The generalizing insight**: the observer's epoch model maps onto
  streams — a source (channel, inbox, repo, metric family) plays the role
  of a session; webhook events accumulate like chunks; epochs form by
  volume/quiet-gap; versioned-prompt distillation + validator teeth +
  privacy contract + tombstones apply unchanged. Build ONE write
  discipline, not a second pipeline.
- **Quality is the charter's soul**: raw webhook flow is high-volume
  garbage. Every quality mechanism proven this week applies: noise bars,
  signals-style pre-mining, validators that refuse, actionability
  requirements, index-lines for the skipped, dedup. "Actionable, useful,
  high quality" is the acceptance test on every ticket here.
- **What exists (verify, don't trust)**: Front + Slack realtime webhooks
  land somewhere in joelclaw (gateway channels / Inngest functions / 110+
  durable fns); ClickHouse blessed for event streams; the Bugle's read-only
  adapters + 4-layer contract + redact.ts; the observer's full machinery.
  GitHub/Twitter have NO known ingress yet.
- **Privacy is sharper here than anywhere**: Front is customer content,
  Slack is third parties. The redaction resolution + secret-scan +
  sensitive-classification apply at full strength; stream observations
  default suspicious.
- **Adjacency**: [observational-memory](./joelclaw-observational-memory-map.svx)
  (machinery reused, boundary redrawn), [recall-consumption](./joelclaw-recall-consumption-map.svx)
  (these pages flow into the same briefing/qmd/Bugle surfaces),
  [bugle redesign](./joelclaw-bugle-redesign-map.svx) (editorial stays there).
- **Skills**: `/skill:wayfinder`, `/skill:axiom-investigation` (log-flow
  archaeology), `/skill:brain-first-workflow`.

## Decisions so far

